genresAdvancedInfo.name: arpa paraguaya
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Arpa paraguaya is a traditional music genre from Paraguay that features the Paraguayan harp as the main instrument. It is characterized by its fast and intricate melodies, which are often accompanied by guitar, percussion, and vocals. The music is deeply rooted in Paraguayan culture and is often associated with celebrations and festivals. It is known for its unique style and has influenced many other genres of music in the region.
